753.question: Is the new model evaluated on the tasks that BERT and ELMo are evaluated on?

4-Table1-1.png: Yes, the new model is evaluated on the same tasks that BERT and ELMo are evaluated on, as indicated by the columns 'BERT', 'ELMo', and 'BERT+ELMo' in the table.</s>

754.question: Does the additional training on supervised tasks hurt performance in some tasks?

4-Table1-1.png: Yes, the additional training on supervised tasks does seem to hurt performance in some tasks. For example, the performance on the MNLI task decreases when fine-tuning on full training data of each target task is applied.</s>

Yes, according to the caption, the additional training on supervised tasks does not always improve performance. For instance, the performance on the MNLI task decreased when fine-tuning on full training data of each target task.</s>
